article.headline: Furman 45, Samford 23
article.story:
GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Daric Carter had two touchdowns and was
one of three Furman tailbacks with 100-plus yards, and Furman beat
Samford 45-23 on Saturday evening.

Carter had 132 yards rushing. He caught a 3-yard touchdown pass
early and had a 57-yard scoring run in the third quarter to put
Furman (2-1) ahead 35-23. It was his first 100-yard rushing game.

Jerome Felton ran for 121 yards and two touchdowns and tailback
Cedrick Gipson added 100 yards rushing and one touchdown.

Jefferson Adcock led Samford (1-2) with 351 yards passing,
completing 31-of-56 passes with a touchdown and two interceptions.
However, the Bulldogs gained just 149 yards in the second half.

Furman scored on its first two possessions of the contest, but
Samford scored 10 unanswered points to cut the lead to 14-10.

The Paladins' Gipson then took an option pitch from Martin and
ran 52 yards for a touchdown before the Bulldogs answered with a
three-play drive that covered 62 yards. The drive ended with
Adcock's 8-yard touchdown pass to Ossie Buchannon, but that was as
close as the Bulldogs would get.
